subsection.def:
court
                    (法院) includes any tribunal or person having
                power to make, confirm, enforce, vary or revoke a maintenance order;

payer
                    (付款人), in relation to a maintenance order,
                means the person liable to make payments under the order;

paragraph.content:
a certificate, signed by the Registrar, certifying that the grounds stated
                    in the certificate are the grounds on which the making of the order might have
                    been opposed by the payer under the order;

subparagraph.content:
made by a court in Hong Kong against a person residing in that country or
                    place;
                        or (Amended 61 of 1981 s. 6)
